title: For Sale:  Savage Model 110BA
location: North Carolina, North Carolina, United States
postcontent: The 338 Lapua is an excellent cartridge for long range sniping and its use in combat sniper rifles continues to grow. Because of the growing adoption among military snipers there has been an increase in popularity among enthusiast as well as competitive shooters in the civilian ranks as well. The downside to the 338 Lapua is that it is based on the .416 Rigby case which has a larger case head diameter (.590 in ) than the standard magnum cases (.532 in ) and unfortunately, many of the commercial actions and bolts are not large enough to easily handle the larger case head diameter. Because of this, popular actions like the Remington 700 require special work to be done to them in order to fit the .338 Lapua, and anytime you mention special work, it means more money and also lower production numbers. As such, there are not a lot of lower priced precision 338 Lapua rifles on the market. That is where the Savage 110 BA comes in. Savage actions are built on a modular design, so instead of them having to make major modifications to a bolt design, they simply had to make a new bolt head and they were pretty much there. Of course some other details such as magazine design needed to be performed as well. The end result is that they were able to release a modern precision sniper rifle chambered in the .338 Lapua for a reasonable price.

postcontent:
I have a Trijicon RX01NSN reflex sight with screw on killflash attachment. It is cosmetically like brand new, and is entirely built to military specifications. There are actuall two versions of this, a civilian version and military version and this is the latter. It has a flat top picatinny rail mount attached and co-witnesses absolutely perfect with the top of a regular F marked AR15 front sight post. It also comes with the threaded killflash attachment to keep from reflecting any light back off the lens.

It uses fiber optics to produce the 4.5 MOA dot during the day and tritium at night, so no batteries required and it's always on and ready to go.

It does have one small polarization flare in the lens which cannot be seen with the killflash attached and does NOT affect the functionality of the sight in any way, shape, or form. I have spoken to Trijicon and confirmed this is entirely normal for this model since it is polarized and have checked on two other of the same model which have the same flares.

To move it fast, and since I do not have the box, I am listing it for about half what they go for new, and the local gun shop has one that is in nowhere near this good of shape for 40.00 more. title: For Sale:  AR-15 50AE ar-50 semi auto 50 ae desert eagle bullet
postcontent:
Up for sale is a AR-15 in 50AE ( that's 50 Action express) which is the desert eagle round, not the 50 BMG military machinegun round. pretty rare. I don't have a chronograph, but fired from a 6" barrel desert eagle pistol the round shoots a 300gr bullet at 1475fps, but this AR barrel is 20" and packs a much bigger punch (probably 1800 to 2000 fps), and even with the AK-74 style muzzle brake on this gun, you know you fired a rifle.  I have shot it less than 10 rounds, so it is basically new, but when I moved to the city, it is pointless for me to keep it. You can see in the picture, the 223 bullet vs the 50 AE bullet.  I chose a 50 AE instead of other big bore thumper AR rounds, as the 50 ae is uncommon, but it is not proprietary like other rounds, so you may be able to find it in gun stores. Comes with 1 10rd magazine, you can easily make more from standard AR mags.

I'm looking mainly for cash, but if you have something to trade, I'll consider offers, but don't waste our time by offering a $600 gun as a even trade. I have a fair amount of other guns too, so if there is something you are looking for, let me know.

I travel a bit between Downriver, Detroit area and Midland/Bay city/Saginaw and occasionally Lansing, so if you are in those areas I may be able to meet you .
